# Backend — Core Rules

`AGENTS.md` (repo root) is the canonical guide; these rules mirror it. When in
doubt, copy the nearest sibling file.

## Stack
Node.js 24 / TypeScript 5 / pnpm / **one Cloudflare Worker** (Hono, deployed via
wrangler) / Neon Postgres (drizzle-orm) / WorkOS JWT / Zod / Biome / Vitest.
No AWS, no CDK, no Lambda, no API Gateway — the Worker IS the edge.

## Critical Invariants
- **No try-catch in route handlers** — `app.ts` `onError` catches and formats every error (`{ success:false, error, details }` wire shape + Sentry capture).
- **Zod for all validation** — REST: `parseBody(rawBody, schema)` (pass `await c.req.text()`, not the request); GraphQL: `schema.parse(input)` in resolvers.
- **Drizzle ORM only** — never raw SQL (migrations are the only SQL).
- **`sanitizeObject()`** on all user input before any DB write.
- **`logAudit()`** on all mutations, fire-and-forget (`void logAudit(...)`); never `await` it on the hot path. The app-level `auditFlush()` middleware drains in-flight writes after every request.
- **ACTIVE filter** on all membership queries: `eq(organizationMembers.status, "ACTIVE")`.
- **Response factories** — REST: `sendSuccess(c, data)` or `createSuccessResponse(data)`; never hand-roll a `Response`/body.
- **Errors factory** — `throw Errors.NotFound("User")` (REST) / `throw new GraphQLError(msg, { extensions: { code } })` (GraphQL); never manual JSON error bodies.
- **CDN URLs only** — `${IMAGES_CDN_URL}/${key}` for images (R2 public/custom-domain URL), never raw bucket URLs.
- **Transactions** for multi-step writes — `db.transaction(async (tx) => { ... })` (works because `lib/db.ts` uses the `neon-serverless` driver; `neon-http` throws on `.transaction()`).
- **DB lifecycle is per-request** — always `await getDb()`; never cache pools/clients at module scope (Workers forbids reusing I/O across requests). The `dbScope()` middleware gives each request its own pool.
- **Auth only from `requireAuth()`** — read `c.get("claims")`; never re-parse JWTs. New protected domains get `routes.use("/v1/<domain>/*", requireAuth())` in `routes/index.ts`.

## Directory Layout
```
src/node/worker.ts           # Worker entry: fetch → app.ts; scheduled → cron.ts registry
src/node/app.ts              # THE Hono app: request-id → dbScope → auditFlush → CORS/security → routes
src/node/routes/             # One Hono sub-app per domain (users.ts, media.ts, graphql.ts, webhooks.ts, utils.ts, test.ts); barrel index.ts mounts them + applies requireAuth()
src/node/cron.ts             # Cron Trigger registry (keys == wrangler.toml [triggers] expressions)
src/node/authorizers/        # verify-token.ts — WorkOS JWT verifier (single source of auth trust)
src/node/handlers/graphql/   # Yoga context, plugins, resolvers/, schema/
src/node/handlers/utils/     # janitor.ts, audit-retention.ts (cron job bodies)
src/node/lib/                # Shared libs (db, errors, audit, sanitize, idempotency, cors, logger, media)
src/node/lib/hono/           # auth (requireAuth), middleware, respond, types (AppEnv)
src/node/lib/validation/     # Zod schemas by domain (users.ts, media.ts, …), re-exported from index.ts
src/node/lib/services/       # Business logic (user-provisioning.ts); routes stay thin
src/node/db/schema/          # Drizzle schema; db/migrations/ holds SQL + journal
wrangler.toml                # Worker config: [vars], R2 bindings, [triggers], env.staging/env.production
scripts/                     # migrate, sync-secrets, deploy, init-project, generate-openapi
```
Layering is strict: `routes → lib/services → lib → db`. Routes orchestrate; they don't hold logic.

## Adding New Code
1. Schema → `src/node/db/schema/{domain}.ts`, export from `index.ts`; `pnpm db:generate` for the migration.
2. Validation → `src/node/lib/validation/{domain}.ts`, export `{domain}Schemas`, re-export from `index.ts`.
3. Logic → `src/node/lib/services/{domain}.ts` if non-trivial; keep route handlers thin.
4. Route → add the handler to `src/node/routes/{domain}.ts` (copy the nearest sibling). New domain: mount in `routes/index.ts` with `requireAuth()` if protected.
5. Scheduled work → register in `cron.ts` + add the `[triggers]` cron in `wrangler.toml` (keys must match byte-for-byte).
6. Test → `tests/unit/{domain}/` (mock DB/Sentry).
7. Run `pnpm check` (Biome lint + `tsc --noEmit` + Vitest) before committing.
